<br>
I just wanted to let everyone know where I have been lately.  Due to real life demands, I have decided to quit DaoC (at least temporarily).  <br>
<br>
As of last Thursday, I was prepared to cancel my account and uninstall DaoC from my hard drive.  Kiz asked me not to (because he knows how much I do enjoy gaming) so I didn’t cancel.  <br>
<br>
The main problem I have is that once I am online, it’s difficult for me to log off or go AFK when I need to.  I often become overly focused on the game, and ignore much of what is going on in real life.  Even though Kiz asked me not to cancel my subscription, due to the intensity of my gaming habits, this might end up to be a permanent decision -- time will tell.<br>
<br>
Gaming is simply taking too much time and energy from me – and it is starting to impact my lifestyle in a negative way.  There are so many things that I would rather be doing than gaming – and so many things in life that I should be doing instead.  <br>
<br>
I have been gaming for quite sometime now.  I think I started massive online gaming way back when The Realm came out.  This is at least 5 years, if not more.  When I started gaming, my life was much different.  Kiz and I were newly married, lived in an easy to maintain townhome, and life was soooo much simpler.  Now, with a toddler, dog and new house with a big yard, longer commutes etc… my lifestyle simply doesn’t allow enough time for online gaming such as DaoC and Everquest.  <br>
<br>
I have met some awesome people in gaming.  I consider some of you closer friends than many other people I consider friends in real life.  I hope we can continue to further these friendships even though I will not be a large part of these online communities anymore.  I still plan on visiting the message boards and helping out with the website, so I will still be around.  If you ever want to chat with me, my MSN email is tiya_archer@hotmail.com.  Feel free to add me to your msn list or send me an email.  I will be on MSN sporadically from now on, but not nearly as much as before – and I really would like to keep in touch.<br>
<br>
Take care everyone, and I wish you all the best. <br>
<br>
Teresa<br>
